</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In legal practice, maintaining the highest standards of professional conduct and ethical behaviour is paramount. The Bar Standards Board (BSB) plays a crucial role in ensuring that barristers in England and Wales adhere to these standards, thereby safeguarding public interest and upholding the integrity of the legal profession. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into the significance of the BSB, key facts and statistics, definitions, and best practices for compliance with relevant legislation and regulations.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-bdc2" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1"><strong>Establishment</strong> - The BSB was established in 2006.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>Scope</strong> - The BSB regulates approximately 16,000 practising barristers.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulatory framework</strong> - The BSB operates under the Legal Services Act 2007.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Complaints</strong> - In 2020-2021, the BSB received over 1,200 complaints, highlighting its active role in maintaining professional standards.

</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Barrister </strong>- A type of lawyer in common law jurisdictions who specialises in courtroom advocacy, drafting legal pleadings, and giving expert legal opinions.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>BSB Handbook</strong> - A comprehensive guide detailing the rules and standards that barristers must follow.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Continuing Professional Development</strong> - Ongoing education that barristers are required to undertake to maintain their professional competence.






</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-41_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-43_ pf-heading-1-h3">Importance of the BSB
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-45_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The BSB ensures public confidence in the legal profession by enforcing high standards of practice and ethical behaviour. It provides a framework for the training and qualification of barristers, monitors compliance with regulatory requirements, and takes disciplinary action when necessary. The BSB's work is crucial in protecting consumers of legal services and maintaining the rule of law.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-47_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-48_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-49_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for compliance
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Adherence to the BSB handbook</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The BSB Handbook outlines the Code of Conduct, and the rules barristers must follow. Barristers should familiarise themselves with the Handbook and ensure their practices align with its provisions. Regular updates and reviews of the Handbook mean continuous compliance attention is necessary.





























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Continuing Professional Development (CPD)</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CPD is a vital component of a barrister's professional development. The BSB mandates that all practising barristers undertake a certain number of CPD hours annually. This ensures that barristers remain knowledgeable about current laws and practices, providing the highest service quality.






























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Complaints and disciplinary procedures</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding the procedures for handling complaints and disciplinary matters is essential. The BSB provides clear guidelines on managing complaints and the steps involved in disciplinary actions. Barristers should establish robust internal procedures to address any complaints efficiently and transparently.






























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-63_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Equality and diversity</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-65_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The BSB significantly emphasises promoting equality and diversity within the legal profession. Barristers and chambers must implement policies that promote an inclusive work environment and comply with anti-discrimination laws.






























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-67_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Risk management</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Effective risk management practices are crucial for compliance. Barristers should regularly assess potential risks in their practice and implement strategies to mitigate them. This includes staying informed about changes in legislation and regulatory requirements.





























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-71_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-72_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-75_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To effectively implement the above best practices, barristers and chambers should consider the following recommendations:



























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-77_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-78_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training and updates </strong>- Engage in regular training sessions on the BSB Handbook and CPD requirements. Utilise resources such as ComplyPlus™ for up-to-date information and training modules.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-80_ pf-text-1"><strong>Develop internal policies</strong> - Create and maintain internal policies that reflect the BSB's standards and guidelines. This includes policies on complaints handling, equality and diversity, and risk management.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-82_ pf-text-1"><strong>Use compliance software</strong> - Implementing compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ can streamline the process of staying compliant with BSB regulations. These tools offer automated updates, training modules, and monitoring features.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-84_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-85_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-86_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
